T1  - Effects of bankruptcy court protection on asset sales
AU  - Pulvino, Todd C.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 52
IS  - 2
SP  - 151
EP  - 186
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/05/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0304-405X(99)00007-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X99000070
KW  - Bankruptcy
KW  - Asset sales
AB  - This paper uses commercial aircraft transactions to determine whether prices obtained from asset sales are greater under Chapter 11 reorganization than under Chapter 7 liquidation. Results indicate that prices obtained under both bankruptcy regimes are substantially lower than prices obtained by non-distressed airlines. Furthermore, there is no evidence that prices obtained by firms reorganizing under Chapter 11 are greater than those obtained by firms liquidating under Chapter 7. An analysis of aircraft sales indicates that Chapter 11 is also ineffective in limiting the number of aircraft sold at discounted prices.
